				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				With the right AAs and the Pet Focus items, your pet can still handle some heavy damage. Mine can take for me in a pinch still at 65, and he regens like some kind of Fungi Monster. 6-7% a /tick/. As soon as I get Pet Discipline, he'll be able to tank most exp mobs indefinately. For those unfamiliar with the trick... You set your pet on a mob, and let him hit it and hopefully taunt and proc a time or two. Then you use '/pet hold'. If he's a focussed pet, he's now regenning faster than most exp mobs can damage him, so he can just sit there and keep the mob's attention until you're ready to kill it.
				
